      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIVIA THEA (7) is first up since finishing seventh (22.56) in a NG at this track over 375m three-and-a-half months ago. Overall form off this box is sound. Drawn wide but with a clean break can feature in the finish. SKEDADDLE PERCY (2) was well back throughout but attacked the line strongly to place, 7 lengths from the winner (30.23) at Nowra in Grade 5. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Leading chance. ADHANA LAYLA (5) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 400m at Mt Gambier, taking a TG1-4W in a quick 23.19. Top win two back and rates a key player again. HARPER (8) is worth some thought after placing at this track and distance last start.",
